abstract: Leaked autopsy report by Maryland medical examiner reveals Freddie Gray's death was ruled homicide due to 'high-energy injury' and failure of police to follow procedure; rules out possibility that death was accidental.
lead_paragraph: A medical examiner found that Mr. Gray sustained the injury while riding in a Baltimore police van and that the failure of the officers to follow procedures meant the death was a homicide.

headline.main: Freddie Gray’s Death Was Homicide, Autopsy Says
headline.print_headline: Gray’s Death Was Homicide, Autopsy Says
